Complexity Analysis
Time Complexity
O(n)

The linked list is traversed only once.

Space Complexity
O(1)

Only a few pointers are used.

Key Concepts Learned
Dummy Node
ListNode dummy = new ListNode(0);
dummy.next = head;

Helps handle deletion of the head node without additional conditions.

Fast & Slow Pointer
fast = fast.next;
slow = slow.next;

Maintains a fixed distance between pointers.

Node Deletion
slow.next = slow.next.next;

Removes a node by bypassing it.

Pattern Learned

Fast & Slow Pointer with Fixed Gap

Move fast pointer ahead by n + 1 steps.
Move both pointers together.
Slow pointer reaches the node before the target.
Delete the target node.

This pattern is commonly used in linked list problems involving:

Finding nodes from the end
Removing nodes
Maintaining a fixed distance between pointers
Takeaway

The optimal solution uses a dummy node and a fixed-gap fast/slow pointer technique to remove the nth node from the end in a single traversal.

Time Complexity: O(n)
Space Complexity: O(1)

